cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image classification using deep learning networks, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the comparison of two different CNN architectures for classification, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning networks for classification also falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the potential use of the method for botanists and camping enthusiasts, which could fall under the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) respectively.
